textAfterTable: Apartment Costs Delvin Jackson - Property Manager Manchester is a relatively affordable cities. This is especially true if you compare the rent to other large cities in the area, for example Boston. Renters can expect to pay under one thousand dollars a month for anything from a one, two or three bedroom apartment. According to this very site, the average rent landlords are asking continues to decline. This is great news if you are looking for a new apartment.   Section 8 & Affordable Delvin Jackson - Property Manager Manchester rates above average when it comes to affordable housing, this includes section 8 housing as well. Like many cities, Manchester has a Housing Authority that is available to assist current and potential residents in their affordable housing search. In addition to the Housing Authority, residents who require assistance can also reach out to: Neighborworks® Greater Manchester, these folks are a non profit that provides housing services in the Manchester, NH area.     We Have 171 Manchester, NH Apartment Listings   Picture
